    "snippet": "On 04/17 around 1500, our Forest Service Radio Banks were showing Link Fail on Arapaho Roosevelt Buckhorn Repeater, DFPC 800, as well as our BLM Repeaters. We called our radio...",
    "narrative": "On 04/17 around 1500, our Forest Service Radio Banks were showing Link Fail on Arapaho Roosevelt Buckhorn Repeater, DFPC 800, as well as our BLM Repeaters. We called our radio technicians immediately to see if we could fix the issue but it seemed to be more of an underlying problem as the hours went by. It was mission critical to get these radio banks back up and running as soon as possible due to resources out in the field relaying information or if there was a fire that was happening, we need these radios to be up and running for communication. We are still currently working on this issue on 04/18. As you know this is a huge safety issue if an incident did happen, we need to be able to communicate with our people out in the field. Dispatchers communicated effectively in the situation as well as our Center Manager, who was trying to solve this problem fast. We have resources that are out in the field at 0800, so again it's mission critical to get these radios back up and running.",
