    "snippet": "• Volunteers borrowed our recently cloned radios for trail work on the Sweet Home Ranger District. When volunteers returned the radios they let me know that neither radio...",
    "narrative": "• Volunteers borrowed our recently cloned radios for trail work on the Sweet Home Ranger District. When volunteers returned the radios they let me know that neither radio worked.  These volunteers are extremely experienced in radio operations.  • I sent a message out to all District employees and asked if others were having issues with the handhelds. Our timber employees responded that their radios are also non-operational. Other departments are checking their radios today.  It appears to be all of the radios (all were cloned the same day).• In talking to other Districts, at least one other is having similar issues. • In talking to the Fire Staff Officer on the Forest, communications is severely understaffed and vacant critical vacancies are impacting the ability for oversight and training.  • We had similar issues last year, so this year we built in mitigations for this years clone and are experiencing the same issues.  We are seeing a pattern of non-operable radios as we move into field season. There are obvious safety issues with employees and volunteers not having communications.• This impacts search and rescue response/coordination with counties,  fire response, RX fire, recreation work, and our ability to keep critical timelines to meet timber targets this year and into the future.  It also impacts our partners and volunteers. Without communications, much of our work cannot be safely accomplished.  • We are requesting a short term solution so that people can safely complete critical work. We are also requesting a long term solution that will decrease that this problem occurs again next year (that would be the third year in a row!).",
    "immediateAction": "• Real time mitigation was to utilize SPOT and Garmin inReach as a communication backup.• Until the issue is solved only employees and partners with secondary communication such as a text capable (2 way communication) satellite devices. We don't have enough of these devices for every field going employee.  Efficiency will be greatly reduced and some timelines for timber targets may slip.  Situations where real time conversations such as fire, emergency, or search and rescue operations will be negatively impacted.",
