    "narrative": "While responding to a mutual aid request, USFS fire personnel discovered they were unable to hit their usual local repeater. After quick troubleshooting, they noted that they were able to receive transmissions, but were unable to transmit over the forest repeater system. This resulted in a delay in response, as the module leader worked to find an operational repeater before responding. An alternate was determined, tested, found to be operational, and the module responded to the incident. Upon further review, personnel discovered that incorrect frequencies had been cloned into all  district handheld and mobile radios during an annual onsite radio update & preventative maintenance inspection that had occurred the day prior.",
    "immediateAction": "The module leader delayed responding to the incident until communications could be confirmed. Once an alternate was confirmed, the module leader confirmed coms with dispatch and responded. After being released from the call, fire personnel reviewed the unit communication plan and compared it to the frequencies found in the radio. It was determined that incorrect tone guards were added during the recent radio maintenance, preventing mobile and handheld radios from transmitting on the primary repeater. The correct transmit tone guards were updated manually, and leadership were notified of the issue.",
