    "snippet": "Module truck was parked inside the fire shop garage for cleaning & restocking in preparation for the fire season. After this was complete, one of the side storage bins on the...",
    "narrative": "Module truck was parked inside the fire shop garage for cleaning & restocking in preparation for the fire season. After this was complete, one of the side storage bins on the passenger side of the truck was left open. This was done at the end of the shift and all personnell were preparing to head home for the day. The driver entered the vehicle and began to pull forward out of the garage in order to park the truck back in its designated spot in the parking lot, without noticing the open bin door. As the truck pulled forward, the open bin door collided with the garage door rail, resulting in damage to the bin door, the garage door rail, and the wall behind it. The driver then backed up, closed the door, and was able to pull the truck out and park without further incident.",
    "immediateAction": "Following this event, all personnell in the unit have placed stronger emphasis on vehicle safety, especially surrounding parking and backing. Stronger precautions include completing a 'golden circle' of a vehicle before the driver enters, checking for any open storage bins, chocks still on the wheels, rocks lodged in between dual tires, or any other safety concerns to be corrected before departing. Another precaution is always using a spotter and/or backer for parking vehicles, reversing, or driving through narrow spaces such as a narrow garage door or narrow road.",
