    "snippet": "Our agency utilizes the Firesponse phone app and web-based service for resource management, fire mapping, and routing. We have found that using this phone app has led to...",
    "narrative": "Our agency utilizes the Firesponse phone app and web-based service for resource management, fire mapping, and routing. We have found that using this phone app has led to decreased situational awareness on the fire ground. Employees are required to enter data into Firesponse upon arrival to active incidents. The result of this, combined with the ongoing technical difficulties while using the phone app, creates a safety issue when incident commanders are spending the initial moments during IA operating their phones instead of doing a traditional size up. This also creates a unprofessional impression with our cooperators who assume we are not actively engaging the fire and using our phones.Firefighters are tasked with using their phones to map fires. The emphasis on mapping fires, even before they are controlled, diminishes the priority of safe suppression tactics. The primary safety concerns are the distracted navigation of terrain, less awareness of roadside and especially overhead hazards, occurring when firefighters are engaged with the phone app. This technology has valid uses in fire management, but the use of it during IA is not one of them.",
    "immediateAction": "These concerns been discussed in several regional and local planning and safety meetings.",
    "mgmtLevel": "N/A",
    "task": "Size Up and Mapping",
