    "snippet": "Communications have gone down for the Redbird Purchase unit due to local community members stealing copper internet lines which has taken the ability to utilize our radio system...",
    "narrative": "Communications have gone down for the Redbird Purchase unit due to local community members stealing copper internet lines which has taken the ability to utilize our radio system for firefighter to communicate to dispatch. This is an ongoing issue over the past 4 years. Dispatch Comms go from the repeaters to a base station to a IP224. The IP224 is internet base which is how our messages in the field get to Winchester Dispatch.This is a huge safety issue for the firefighters in the field; we are in peak prescribe fire and wildland fire seasons. The Redbird District relies on Radios and Repeaters due to the limited cell service coverage in the area due to the steep rugged terrain. We have expressed our concerns in the past with how often the Copper lines have been stolen. The internet company has started to install lines that are tracked by GPS but it still continues to occur.One solution is to install Low Level satellite-based internet (starlink)to provide constant coverage for firefighter to contact dispatch, we have a Starlink at the repeater site of our base station, but the district has been waiting on CIO to send a Switch for the IPP224 to be able to work with the Starlink which was installed 4 months ago.",
