    "snippet": "The release of IQCS 2.x has had unexpected impacts across the nation for resource ordering in IROC.1)\tAn unknown group of resources are showing now as uncertified or as False in...",
    "narrative": "The release of IQCS 2.x has had unexpected impacts across the nation for resource ordering in IROC.1)\tAn unknown group of resources are showing now as uncertified or as False in their qualifications2)\tNot all qualifications are impacted.  Higher level qualifications may not be available but lower level qualifications are available for selection.3)\tCertifying officials cannot certify personnel even though they have the correct permissions to do the certification of the resource.Work around:  Forest Training officer and forest must re-certify person in IQCS.  This must be done resource by resource.  Once the user is set in IQCS, the resource moves through the system into IROC and is available for re-assignmentSafety Issues1)\tTime – delay in filling resources due to ‘fixing’ personnel2)\tAccuracy – Filling personnel with lower quals and sending to fill ‘higher’ positions.  Possible legal ramifications if documentation does not match the job resource is filling.3)\tReassignment – persons on assignment prior to release of IQCS 2.x cannot be re-assigned as the quals are not available to place the resource.4)\tIROC steps for filling out of local area – dispatch centers are to ‘…Filling dispatch centers, will claim the order and will add documentation to the request to include: name of individual filling the request, their host unit, and travel information.  Filling dispatch centers will then make positive communication with the ordering dispatch center to notify the fill of the request.”.  The fire that did the request now has Pending orders that are ‘filled’ but no way to see what is filled.  Dispatch has to read every resource to see if it is filled.  This again takes time from doing other work tasks.5)\tResource on the fire – e-ISuite  has no tracking of the resource from IROC.6)\tMany resources only get to participate for one assignment per season.  If this is the one assignment, there is no tracking of this assignment in IROC.  There is no record that they did competencies at a position if the resource or is filled with a lower qualification or not filled in at all.My two CIMT incidents and Type 3 incident is being impacted by this.  I know the issue is being worked by the developers.  I wanted others to be aware of issues listed and others that are not identified here.",
    "immediateAction": "Work around:  Forest Training officer and forest must re-certify person in IQCS.  This must be done resource by resource.  Once the user is set in IQCS, the resource moves through the system into IROC and is available for re-assignment",
    "mgmtLevel": "1",
    "task": "IROQ processing of orders",
