    "snippet": "march of 2026 IQCS 2.0 rolled out. During this time not all qualification moved into the new system. This also included resources in IROC not showing their current qualification....",
    "narrative": "march of 2026 IQCS 2.0 rolled out. During this time not all qualification moved into the new system. This also included resources in IROC not showing their current qualification. Now fast forward to 03/12/2026 when other forest / units within the Rocky Mountain GACC start to have large fires and the mobing of CIMT's are being ordered. Now Team members, and other resources are not being ordered the normal way because IQCS 2.0, IROC and IRWIN aren't talking. This is making more work on the tier two and three centers to make, send and fill resources for these emerging incidents. We have to do double work and are possibly making duplicate resources in IROC or they are not able to fill the orders the normal way. This also is impacting the centers as force fill in IROC was removed last season. There are currently four large fires in the state of Nebraska, of which one of them is currently 330,000ac, and there are other fires in South Dakota that centers in the RMA are trying to fill CIMT(s) orders and our hands are tied. With the current push of IQCS 2.0 there is account managers and certifying officials that are unable to fix the qualification issue and have had to put tickets into IRWIN with no results at this current time.",
