    "snippet": "Numerous times the zone select collar/knob (A B C D knob) on BKR5000 radios get jostled, resulting in the radio changing to a home zone. The beep notification when this happens...",
    "narrative": "Numerous times the zone select collar/knob (A B C D knob) on BKR5000 radios get jostled, resulting in the radio changing to a home zone. The beep notification when this happens is often not heard due to environmental noise. This results in important frequencies not being monitored despite the radio being on. In this particular case our radios continued to pick up the local tax and crew channels, due to PScan being set to a crew channel and R8 and R9 sharing a tac frequency. A/G and command frequencies were not being scanned for unknown amounts of time. This has not yet resulted in any harm, but myself and my crew believe it to be a serious concern.",
    "immediateAction": "Control lock switch did not lock out use of zone select knob. Properly set priority scan can mitigate lack of communication when zones are unintentionally switched. Home forest has no radio tech and we do not have any easy way to disable this feature, despite mentioning it before our 2026 clone was distributed.",
