    "narrative": "While en route to the Turkey Foot and Wilburn Ford RX, the RXB2 (XXX) called dispatch and asked if comms were coming over the radio because resources were trying to call out. The dispatcher informed the RXB2 that no radio transmissions had come over the radio. The RXB2 and dispatcher did a radio check on both repeaters (Blk War and Blk Pond) without success. It was decided by the RXB2 to establish communication through text messaging. Text messaging/phone call communications is unreliable due to intermittent phone service depending on terrain and topography. Unreliable communication poses a serious threat to wildland firefighting safety. If an incident within an incident were to occur, a medical emergency for example, without reliable comms with dispatch delay in medical care could be life threatening. With more adequate time, other reliable means of communication could have been established, or the radio tech may have been able to assess the radio equipment for possible factors affecting radio transmissions.",
