    "snippet": "FICC San Bernadino has been experiencing power outages that have affected resources in the field. I have several critical issues regarding the reliability of our dispatch...",
    "narrative": "FICC San Bernadino has been experiencing power outages that have affected resources in the field. I have several critical issues regarding the reliability of our dispatch services and radio functionality.During the major outage on January 3rd over (25) law enforcement rangers were put in a very unsafe environment. With no emergency communications. During this same event rangers had contacted a felon in possession of a firearm. The job of a law enforcement Ranger is inherently dangerous already without the limited ability to request emergency assistance! These radio issues are a known concern and have been over several years! It’s often laughed about at large incident inbriefs that it’s not if we loose comms it’s we will lose them! This is extremely concerning and brings up the concern of what will it take to fix the issue. Will it take rangers loosing their lives? Will it take the leadership having to walk to the front door at my residence to tell my wife, four year old daughter and 1 year old son that daddy isn’t coming home because no one answered the radio when he needed help? What will it take? I’m very curious! The current year is 2026 and technology has advanced! Why haven’t we? Is it the funding? What’s it going to cost? The lives of one Ranger, maybe two, maybe three…….I have expressed concerns to the communication employees. I have asked what’s the solution. I have asked why! The answer is funding! Do we need to help solve the issue by escalating it to higher levels? I hope that solution is reachable immediately.",
