    "snippet": "On November 27, 2025, while dispatching for a law enforcement event from FICC, I experienced multiple power fluctuations that severely impacted operational capabilities. The...",
    "narrative": "On November 27, 2025, while dispatching for a law enforcement event from FICC, I experienced multiple power fluctuations that severely impacted operational capabilities. The building currently relies on an emergency generator due to a compromised and unstable electrical system, with a permanent fix reportedly delayed by an estimated 3–4 months.During the incident, these power fluctuations caused entire dispatch consoles to restart, radio systems to freeze, and communication channels to lock out dispatchers. These failures directly interfered with our ability to maintain continuous communication with Law Enforcement, Fire, and EMS resources, placing both responders and the public at significant risk.This situation represents a critical safety concern. Power instability in a dispatch center can lead to equipment malfunctions, data loss, and system outages, severely compromising the center’s ability to coordinate emergency response efforts in real time. In high-stakes environments such as wildland fire management and emergency services, even brief interruptions can delay resource deployment, hinder situational awareness, and increase the risk to field personnel and the communities we serve.",
    "immediateAction": "To ensure operational resilience and responder safety, it is imperative that robust power management systems be implemented immediately. This includes surge protection, uninterruptible power supplies (UPS), and reliable backup generators, along with expedited repairs to the primary electrical infrastructure.",
    "mgmtLevel": "N/A",
    "task": "",
    "resources": "Law Enforcement/EMS",
