    "snippet": "Fire Reporting/Phone Issues: Dispatch Center's phone number not connecting or call-forward function not working correctly.Events: Federal Interagency dispatch center's phones do...",
    "narrative": "Fire Reporting/Phone Issues: Dispatch Center's phone number not connecting or call-forward function not working correctly.Events: Federal Interagency dispatch center's phones do not connect to incoming calls after hours. AZ State Dispatch Center called Williams Interagency Dispatch Center (WIDC) the evening of 11.11- 2330 to report a Vehicle/Wildfire along I-40 in Northern Arizona. Per Az State dispatch, when dialing the center's main number, the call would not connect. State dispatch then called the local state Fire Department to respond to the fire report. On 11.12.2025 at 0700hrs, Az State dispatch center called WIDC and relayed fire report [az-WDC-101029] (no issues with phone connection at this time).  Federal resources were then made aware of the incident. There was no known phone outage reported for the evening of 11.11.2025",
    "immediateAction": "11.12.2025 @ 0830 Center Manager Actions: *Checked all WIDC Phones located at the center, no record of in-coming calls from the night of 11.11-12.2025 @ 2300-000Hrs. *Called Answering Service -No record of any incoming calls to WIDC 11.11.2025 2100 11.12.2025-0100hrs*Called AZ State evening (11.11.25) dispatcher and she verified that the correct phone number was dialed. The main phone number would not connect.  *Open a Phone Repair Incident with the CIO to report the issue on 11.12.2025 1000hrs and documented all events WIDC WildCAD Incident AZ-WDC-001030.",
