    "snippet": "11/07/2025At 0822, Dispatch received a smoke report of “a tree on fire” up the North Fork near Libby Creek and notified the DO to send a response. Resources responded. By 1105,...",
    "narrative": "11/07/2025At 0822, Dispatch received a smoke report of “a tree on fire” up the North Fork near Libby Creek and notified the DO to send a response. Resources responded. By 1105, the NZ DO (XXX) called via landline to conduct a radio check on the Clayton Mountain repeater; there was no contact on either end. The DO decided resources would not engage given the terrain and bear country. Resources began returning to quarters at 1115.The dispatcher contacted radio technician XXX regarding the Clayton Mountain repeater being down. XXX called back and stated, “XXX will be over to Cody Monday to get everything packaged up and ready to go for the Clayton repeater mission on Tuesday and Wednesday (11/11–11/12).”11/13/2025At 1053, Dispatch received an email from XXX and AOB XXX requesting an order for the NOCO T3 helicopter for the following day to complete the repeater mission. XXX then called Dispatch to let us know that the GACC was aware of the order being placed, as this was a GACC-to-GACC arrangement to obtain the helicopter for the mission. Dispatch created the order and placed it up.At 1057, XXX sent another email stating, “Thanks XXX, I am still unable to contact any of the radio folks which of course is the crux of the whole operation. I will update when I hear back from them.”At 1140, XXX sent a follow-up email stating, “Radio techs are not in a position to make this mission work. Go ahead and cancel the helicopter order. They are working on a portable repeater work around for the North Fork.” Dispatch then retrieved the order and notified RMACC that the mission was off.At 1213, XXX called Dispatch asking if there was a BLM repeater in the North Fork corridor coverage area that could provide similar coverage to Clayton. The dispatcher informed him that no, the only BLM repeater in that area is Cedar Mountain, which is located right next to NZ Direct. XXX stated that since they could not have everything ready for a helicopter mission, they would be testing the NZ portable repeater with Dispatch shortly to ensure it works, and then XXX would be putting it in place once they identify an accessible high point that will cover the North Fork.Dispatch understands how mission-critical the Clayton repeater is, especially given the limited favorable weather windows between now and spring. There are no accessible high points that resources can reach on foot to install a portable repeater capable of providing coverage comparable to Clayton. Numerous prescribed fire pile units are located throughout the North Fork corridor on the Shoshone National Forest, and they are not operationally accessible without a functional Clayton repeater. Although there are alternative methods for field resources to reach Dispatch without the repeater, those options are not consistently reliable.",
    "immediateAction": "Notified USFS Radio Techs, and submitted ticket ID2755645. Ordered a helicopter for the mission.",
