    "snippet": "While using the BKR 5000 the ‘quick-zone’ selector knob located below the channel selector can become inadvertently bumped. This unintentional selection can result in the radio...",
    "narrative": "While using the BKR 5000 the ‘quick-zone’ selector knob located below the channel selector can become inadvertently bumped. This unintentional selection can result in the radio not functioning as intended. The concern issue being that a period could go by before you realize that communications have been missed, which results in any number of errors and unfortunate results. Seeking a solution to disable that collar thus avoiding communication breakdowns.I have recently seen a similar safe net addressing this topic and I wanted to offer support and establish the trend that this has happened to more than one person. In my time using the BKR 5000 I have seen this error occur commonly. I have taken this up with the forest / regional radio person no acceptable solution has been offered.",
    "immediateAction": "The current solution I've been able to discover is to constantly and frantically look at my radio ensuring that I am still in the correct zone.",
