    "snippet": "Command of the wildcat fire was transferred from a SE Washington type 3 team back to the local unit on 9/29/2025. The existing ICP was vacated, the national caterer was released,...",
    "narrative": "Command of the wildcat fire was transferred from a SE Washington type 3 team back to the local unit on 9/29/2025. The existing ICP was vacated, the national caterer was released, and a new ICP was established at the Chinook Pass Work Center. A local restaurant called “XXX XXX” took on the catering responsibilities for all resources assigned to the incident.The restaurant is set up buffet style, such that firefighters park outside, walk into the restaurant through the main entry doors, and proceed directly to the serving area. The food is served in large serving trays with a set of serving utensils for each dish.There is no handwashing station immediately available to use en route from the parking lot to the buffet, and the vast majority of personnel on the incident are not washing their hands between the time when they leave the line and when they touch the serving utensils. Additionally, there is no sneeze guard present to protect the food from contamination from airborne saliva/mucus droplets.As of 10/2/2025 there are approximately 150 people assigned to the incident, with more resources checking in daily.",
    "immediateAction": "This issue was brought to the attention of the safety officer assigned to the fire on the morning of 10/1/2025. A Small, portable foot-pump style hand wash station was placed below an embankment and out of view of the parking lot and the entry doors to the restaurant. The safety officer reminded some people to wash their hands, but most folks still are not doing so. The presence of the hand wash station is not known to most, so almost nobody is using it.There has not been a strong announcement during briefing stating that hand washing is required prior to touching the serving utensils.There is still no sneeze guard present over the food.Total personnel assigned to the incident is approximately 150 and growing.",
    "mgmtLevel": "3",
    "task": "Meals",
    "resources": "All resources assigned to fire",
