    "snippet": "Poor Network (Internet)service to Williams Interagency Dispatch Center and sponsoring Kaibab NF SO.  Weather was no factor: partly sunny skies and seasonable temperatures. The...",
    "narrative": "Poor Network (Internet)service to Williams Interagency Dispatch Center and sponsoring Kaibab NF SO.  Weather was no factor: partly sunny skies and seasonable temperatures. The center supports Fire & Aviation operations for the Kaibab NF, Grand Canyon NP, Hualapai Tribal Forestry. Dispatch services are being compromised due to employees being unable to fully access Computer Aid Dispatch programs (WildCAD-E, IROC, AFF) to support fire & aviation operations: flight-following of aircraft, tracking of field and fire going resources, document incident events, accessing/providing weather updates to wildfire resources. A complex management incident (Dragon Bravo/AZ-GCP-000597) with an expanded dispatch organization hosted by the local dispatch center is being hampered due to network issues: Resource Ordering is delayed due to network limits.Safety Issues: Dispatchers are under stress trying to complete assignments and are unable to perform their duties at a quality level. Possible missing documentation of incident events/response, flight-following of aircraft and tracking filed going resources.  With no full-time local IT/Radio staff, dispatch management is taking way from overseeing the operation of the center to preform IT trouble-shooting actions and submitting service repairs to address network issues.",
    "immediateAction": "Correction: The Center Manager restarted the dispatch computers with no success. Computers still have limited access to multiple CAD Systems.   The USFS CIO desk was contacted by the Center Manager and a repair ticket was created.   COOP Ops: The Center Manager utilized spare laptops and mobile hotspots, along with using NPS/DOI computers to access dispatch programs.   This was immediate work around the issue, providing service to all customers of the dispatch center.",
