    "snippet": "On August 27th,2025 I took IC of the bravo fire. It was reported as a single tree even though the night before I called it in as a tree with ground fire along with another...",
    "narrative": "On August 27th,2025 I took IC of the bravo fire. It was reported as a single tree even though the night before I called it in as a tree with ground fire along with another engine. A patrol and I made access off the decommissioned road and hiked to the ridge to gain access to the fire. Once we came upon the fire, we realized that it was not going to be safe nor possible for us to engage safely. Due to 10-15-foot-tall brush, heavy dead and down, old, unburned hand piles and multiple snags in the area, while on step unforgiving ground. With snags actively burning about 50 feet up, 2/3 ways burnt through and throwing pieces of burning material down upon us. I constructed saw line on the decommissioned road for access to the fire but wasn't able to construct line to due safety concerns.Additionally, we had the blue fire approximately a mile away actively picking up with extreme fire behavior moving towards us, which resources had already pulled off. During this fire BC actively undermined the IC and on multiple occasions ignored the IC and her updates to dispatch and resources on the fire. BC disregarded ICs experience and concerns for the safety of her resources. BC made remarks to resources that IC 'is just bullheaded and hard to work with'. BC tried to intimated IC to engage and fall the snag on the fire, while resources on the fire also voiced their concerns of safety and not wanting to engage. While the Sawyer also declined felling of the snag and felt uncomfortable working on the fire due to all of the safety concerns above. Resources stated they could feel the hostility of BC towards the IC.",
    "immediateAction": "I continued open communication with my local dispatch and resource on the fire about fire activity and pulled resources off the fire. I also tried to communicate with BC on multiple occasions, on multiple radio channels about the activity of the fire without any response from his end. I continued to monitor the fire   in hopes that the snag would fall, and we could safely re-engage.",
