    "snippet": "During the initial attack, and throughout the duration of the West Fork fire, it was noticed that several of the forest repeaters were/are severely lacking in providing adequate...",
    "narrative": "During the initial attack, and throughout the duration of the West Fork fire, it was noticed that several of the forest repeaters were/are severely lacking in providing adequate communications with the local unit and dispatch center. The repeaters are linked through an intricate maze of connections to provide communications to Billings Dispatch Center. However, the maze of connections are faulty, inconsistent, and unreliable. This lack of consistent communications provided several safety issues for crews, the management team and the dispatch center.",
    "immediateAction": "As soon as the issues were identified, orders were placed for Comm techs to be on site in order to help sleuth out the issues with the repeater network. Additionally, a mobile repeater was ordered and placed on the incident which significantly improved communications for the type 3 team, and the resources on the incident. Unfortunately, these band-aid fixes didn't fix the ultimate problem. There have been several tickets submitted for help with the network issues that seem to be the pivotal link to providing consistent communications.",
