    "snippet": "Upon initial attack of the Tammarack and Jim fires, the incident commanders were unable to get positive communications dispatch on Slate Peak or Granite, forest repeaters. Their...",
    "narrative": "Upon initial attack of the Tammarack and Jim fires, the incident commanders were unable to get positive communications dispatch on Slate Peak or Granite, forest repeaters. Their transmission was perfectly clear over the air and into dispatch, however, dispatch was unable to transmit to the field on either repeater. A volunteer lookout was able to relay, but this caused excess traffic on repeaters during a busy lightning bust. This also results in a single conduit for communication to and from dispatch, which is not ideal. That lookout is not staffed every single day of fire season, and with a human in the chain, she is susceptible to many possible reasons why she isn't able to answer the radio. We have had this issue with our repeaters this year, and it has been fixed on our other repeaters. The issue persists.",
    "immediateAction": "Repeatedly raising the issue to the radio shop, district ranger, and forest level fire leadership. Was difficult to get any action out of the radio shop previously on this issue, tickets were closed saying the repeaters were functioning normally when the issue had not changed at all.",
