    "snippet": "Got a report of a wildfire along the CO/WY border and was told an engine would be responding. When I got into the dispatch center there was a Link Fail on the one radio bank I...",
    "narrative": "Got a report of a wildfire along the CO/WY border and was told an engine would be responding. When I got into the dispatch center there was a Link Fail on the one radio bank I needed to use to talk with the engine crew. Being that the engine is responding late at night and dispatch has no comms with them is a potentially dangerous scenario.",
    "immediateAction": "Called radio techs, looked at Xymon site, and talked with DO. Multiple attempts were tried to reach the engine with no luck. I was able to hear and talk to the DO  who was on a radio in the district office. Restarted C-Soft console and tried reaching the engine again. The engine was able to hear dispatch but dispatch could not hear them. It seems there is one way audio on multiple base stations. The DO is continuing to track the engine since dispatch is unable to talk to them.",
