    "snippet": "Around 1600 we noticed that when people called in they were not able to hear us respond. Everything on the radio looked like it was working. The sounds bar was showing noise...",
    "narrative": "Around 1600 we noticed that when people called in they were not able to hear us respond. Everything on the radio looked like it was working. The sounds bar was showing noise levels, the TX mode would kick on, we did not have a link fail and sometimes it would give kick back. We tried calling out on multiple radio consoles and were not successful. At this point we reached out to the districts to see if the base radios were working. We had figured out that the base radios could talk to each other (North and South) but were not able to hear us. This leads us to believe it is a Lumen connection issue. Our main radio is out of North Zone (NURD) and in order for the center to broadcast out it has to push through the Lumen network. I believe the link between the forest service network and Lumen continues to go out and it does not allow us to talk to the field. We are working to set up a COOP plan in NURD which would allow us to function but it is a 30 min drive. That drive time takes critical time away from dispatchers and the field during emergencies. We also share our veg file with multiple centers but that link has to run through Lumen which is what is continuing to fail.",
    "immediateAction": "Dispatch started calling all duty officers and letting them know about the issue, a ticket was put in, radio tech was notified, and an email was sent out. We are unable to correct this problem and we have to wait for the network to come back up to link our radios back to our main repeater.",
    "mgmtLevel": "N/A",
