    "snippet": "At 0915 our Columbine District FMO advised dispatch that someone's 'squirrel channel' was bleeding over into our Pargin and Grassy repeaters, bogging up our most accessible...",
    "narrative": "At 0915 our Columbine District FMO advised dispatch that someone's 'squirrel channel' was bleeding over into our Pargin and Grassy repeaters, bogging up our most accessible repeaters for that district.",
    "immediateAction": "Durango Dispatch proceeded to attempt to break into the traffic to advise them that they were bleeding over to our command repeater. Dispatchers deduced that they could not receive our traffic and that they had Pargin's transmit frequency and tone, but not the receive. DRC Dispatchers proceeded to call all fires in zone to try to narrow down what crew could be bleeding over. Deduced that it was not any resources in our zone and began to look at fires surrounding. Spoke with Santa Fe regarding their Laguna Fire. Started listening for names and identifiable information and was able to copy a few names. Durango dispatchers then took to IROC to find a crew that had individuals matching the names mentioned. We found those names matching up to a crew on the Deer Creek Fire. Durango dispatchers called Moab Dispatch and advised of the situation, which was referred over to their Radio Tech. Radio Tech contacted DRC and we gave the identifiable information to him to assist finding the crew in question. He successfully did so and advised the crew to cease and desist in using that frequency. Which they did.",
