    "snippet": "The US NPS GCP North Rim AA’s have been pressuring non -stop to cut trees in and around the North rim admin site, lost historic lodge, and the many lost cabins and structures...",
    "narrative": "The US NPS GCP North Rim AA’s have been pressuring non -stop to cut trees in and around the North rim admin site, lost historic lodge, and the many lost cabins and structures devastated by the Dragon Bravo Fire. GCP would not bring in an outside consult and assessment of the known hazmat site, on any terms. Instead they brought in their own hazmat specialist who took air monitor samples for less than one day, and selectively released a tailored report, stating that there is no risk or hazard associated with the said fire destroyed structures.",
    "immediateAction": "Several accounts are reported of private meetings bullied and pressured by Park service AA’s, pushing management to allow use of firefighters in and around the known hazmat site, to fell over 1,000 trees that had been marked as “hazard”, even when operational overhead after operational overhead had stated that the hazard work had been long completed. The non hazard marked trees seemed to align with view shed and potential new building sites instead.",
