    "snippet": "During the initial attack of fire #423, the Salmon Fire, I experienced periods of missed communication due to radio issues with the new BKR-5000. I was the IC-4 trainee of the...",
    "narrative": "During the initial attack of fire #423, the Salmon Fire, I experienced periods of missed communication due to radio issues with the new BKR-5000. I was the IC-4 trainee of the fire and communicating with resources on the opposite flank as they coordinated use of aircraft and priority areas of concern. When receiving  transmissions from other firefighters my radio would cut out if anyone one else came within a few hundred feet of me. I could hear that transmissions were still coming across because I could hear them on other radios, however I was not receiving them. This created a few instances that I was missing key tactical information in a timely manner.",
    "immediateAction": "The only solution that I discovered for the duration of the fire was to have anyone close to me turn off their radio if I needed to talk with someone. There was no other solutions that we could come up with. Changing the antennas and adding guards had no effect on the issue.",
