    "snippet": "For over the last month we have been experiencing issues with the internet at the Challis Helibase. We have had numerous tickets for similar issues in the past. On June 26, 2025...",
    "narrative": "For over the last month we have been experiencing issues with the internet at the Challis Helibase. We have had numerous tickets for similar issues in the past. On June 26, 2025 the internet stopped working. Initially we filed a ticket and our communication tech to stop by and look at the problem. He determined it was the network and elevated the case up. As of now, the issue has not been fixed. Now we are in the heart of fire season and can not receive or transmit radio communications to resources or dispatch. This has created a safety issue for operations.“Telex Radio IP (network) Console is inoperable due to lack of USDA.net hardline ethernet connection, which is required due to RolP constraints and multicast needs.Immediate service restoration required for Safe Operations at the Challis Air Base during active IA and sustained fire fighting efforts. Forest Fire Danger Level elevated, need for Radio IP Console to be fully in service and reliable.Telex IP Console information:IP - XXXSub net - XXXDG - XXX  - Challis Radio Tech",
    "immediateAction": "We have filed tickets with CHD and have talked to our radio tech. Unfortunately our radio tech is not able to remedy the issue due the network being inoperable. The problem is still on going",
