    "snippet": "The North Kaibab just had our radio System updated with the new internet and our internet capabilities can't handle it. Our local resources half the time can't here our dispatch...",
    "narrative": "The North Kaibab just had our radio System updated with the new internet and our internet capabilities can't handle it. Our local resources half the time can't here our dispatch center Williams Dispatch, so traveling around the district and on projects this is a huge safety concern for our resources. We had the Tater fire on 6/9/25 the resources could call William's dispatch but could not hear Williams responding back so we had to have someone at the district office relay with dispatch this is a continuing problem day after day not just on the Fireline. Again on 6/11/25 we had the Mason fire and had to use the Grand Canyon repeater system to talk with dispatch. We even had XXXX a fixed wing detection plane flying the district and they could not communicate with Williams on our Big Ridge repeater. If we don't have someone at the district office to relay this is a big safety concern, we have for the ground resources on a day-to-day operation.",
