    "snippet": "On a daily bases for quite sometime now our Forest Service Network has been slow and at times unusable. I manage an Emergency Command Center (Dispatch) that requires reliable...",
    "narrative": "On a daily bases for quite sometime now our Forest Service Network has been slow and at times unusable. I manage an Emergency Command Center (Dispatch) that requires reliable network connectivity to multiple computer applications. Having network issues that either won't work at all or limits what applications you can access is unacceptable and becomes a huge safety issue to our firefighters and law enforcement officers.At our center we dispatch for two forests. One of the forests depends on our ability to communicate on the radio using Radio-Over-IP. (Internet). If the internet is slow or non-functional then communications suffer. Today I'm tracking aircraft going to and from incidents around our region and I have to use our state partner's network in order to perform my assigned duties.Other programs such as EGP, WIMS, IROC and other supportive programs are having intermittent operational issues and sometimes unable to access at all. My center does not use WildCAD-e but most of the others in my region do and rely on the internet to actually dispatch incident. When CAD is down, Dispatch is down which means large delays in response of Emergency Resources.",
    "immediateAction": "Multiple service tickets have been submitted and they tell us that the problem is fixed or no problem was found, however these issue are either not fixed or return.",
