    "factors": [
      "Communications"
    ],
    "snippet": "Central CA Interagency Communications Center (CCICC) 'Porterville' Radios have been intermittent and not working in areas since May 25, 2025. On the Cotton Incident (CA-CND)...",
    "narrative": "Central CA Interagency Communications Center (CCICC) 'Porterville' Radios have been intermittent and not working in areas since May 25, 2025. On the Cotton Incident (CA-CND) where both CND and SQF resources were dispatched the IC's for the BLM and USFS had problems making communication with Porterville Dispatch. It was also reported by the Hume Lake Ranger District that they had communications issues over the Memorial Day weekend holiday communicating with CCICC. Our LMR Radio Techs for the Sequoia are aware of the situation and identified the problem as the microwave links for the forest. From my inquiries with the Radio Techs it sounds like it is a training issue on the new microwave links that were installed and the new microwave links not being programmed correctly when they were delivered by the vendor. The Radio Techs are scheduled to attend a training on the new microwave link. We are in fire/field season and not having a working radio system to provide critical communications is a major safety issue for field, law enforcement, and fire personnel.",
    "immediateAction": "If users cannot reach Porterville dispatch by Radio, landline the ECC. Non-Fire field going personal, do not go into the field unless necessary. If you do please made check-in plans with your supervisor or coworkers.   We have Radio Tech’s working on the issue and will update when we have additional information.Our Center Managers through our coop plan have identified that using cooperating agencies radio communications as a back-up is an option and they have worked with other local cooperators to make them aware of the issue and made an agreement to use their systems as a backup for running emergency incidents.",
    "mgmtLevel": "N/A",
