    "snippet": "AFS Radio Shop – Galena Radio Loop Communications Summary (May 13, 2025)On May 13, 2025, AFS Radio Shop initiated radio loop operations in Galena. The first segment of the loop...",
    "narrative": "AFS Radio Shop – Galena Radio Loop Communications Summary (May 13, 2025)On May 13, 2025, AFS Radio Shop initiated radio loop operations in Galena. The first segment of the loop reaches the Totson Mountain repeater site. Since the Totson Mountain repeater remains offline during the winter months, flight following for this mission is typically conducted via satellite phone.We generally rely on the Galena Station phone system to maintain consistent communication with aircraft. With the station opening on May 1, 2025, it was assumed that the phone system would be operational upon the arrival of core staff on May 12, 2025. However, the phones were not active, requiring dispatch to fall back on a contingency plan involving an outdated hardline phone (circa late 1980s to early 1990s). This phone has known reliability issues, with both the receiver speaker and microphone intermittently cutting out—especially problematic during satellite phone communications.Although replacement of the Galena Station phones has been scheduled for several years, to our knowledge, the project has repeatedly been deferred due to lack of funding.",
    "immediateAction": "Mitigation MeasuresAs a dispatcher in remote western Alaska, adaptability is essential. To offset the poor audio quality on the legacy phone, we utilized Wi-Fi calling via cell phones when communication over the coop line became unintelligible. However, this workaround also carries inherent safety concerns, as the internet connection in the area is frequently unstable and unreliable.When the phone outage was discovered, notifications were sent to YFDC CM/IT/GAL Logistics and the Galena Duty Officer (DO) on May 12, 2025.",
