    "snippet": "On 5/6/2025 BIA conducted bucket operations with a National Guard CH-47. Traininghad been planned for a couple of weeks. Prior to training beginning BIA called toconfirm that...",
    "narrative": "On 5/6/2025 BIA conducted bucket operations with a National Guard CH-47. Traininghad been planned for a couple of weeks. Prior to training beginning BIA called toconfirm that dispatch was still good for training. Dispatch informed BIA we werestill good and there was no planned aerial operations in the area of Indian Lake.BIA was informed that ODF Black Mtn was still down. Advised to try Tower Mtn andTip Top. Dispatcher was unaware that Tip top was also down because it is tied toODF Black Mtn.National Guard pilot called and made sure we could talk on national for flightfollowing. I gave him the centers La Grande Air flight follow frequencyinformation. National Guard pilot was unsure if he would be able to program theradio due to some other circumstances. Dispatcher confirmed that aircraft did nothave AFF with national guard pilot. National guard pilot informed dispatcher thatthey would probably show up on ADS-B while enroute to training area, but oncebuckets started they would probably fall off of ADS-B.National guard pilot called on national, flight following was established with 15minute check ins.Dispatcher tried to call BIA via radio. Tip Top first then Tower Mountain toinform aircraft was enroute. Dispatch called person in charge was unable to reachthem via phone call went to message. Dispatch was unable to make positivecontact with BIA to inform them of aircraft enroute.The concern is that because the repeater has been out of service for extendedamounts of time, resources may have forgot it is not working. If the helicopterwere to have an incident at the training site, no communication could be made atthe site with dispatch to help facilitate a response. No radio coverage, no cellcoverage and no AFF.",
    "immediateAction": "Continued verbal flight following checks every 15 minutes.Continued monitoring ADS-B.Informed supervisor, suggested we send out a message weekly that repeater andchannels are still down for SA.",
    "mgmtLevel": "N/A",
