    "snippet": "Shasta-Trinity National ForestShasta Lake District Office RADIO,Internet, and phone OutageWe have been experiencing internet issues since May 5, 2025.  Several tickets have been...",
    "narrative": "Shasta-Trinity National ForestShasta Lake District Office RADIO,Internet, and phone OutageWe have been experiencing internet issues since May 5, 2025.  Several tickets have been placed with CIO. On May 12th the wireless internet was working, and our phones and radio stayed online temporarily.  Network outage (including RADIO affecting emergency communications) was reported  on June 19, 2025, Request ID REQ000005357403.  On June 23, 2025 reply to email sent stated that a technician would come out to fix the problem, but not until June 30th which leaves us vulnerable for another 7 days.Currently we are in staffing level 3.  IA has been moderate over the last two weeks due to lightning activity and wind events.  Currently our district is experiencing temperatures above 100 degrees, winds and lightning is expected this coming week.  We are facing a tremendous deficit by not being able to pick up all radio communications on our handheld radios missing simultaneously broadcasts, such as IA response, extended staffing, daily weather,  etc. This also effects our decision making and situational awareness not having direct contact with dispatch.Firefighter Safety is in jeopardy on our District due to this outage not being taken seriously.",
