    "snippet": "Internet went down here at the Springerville Supervisors Office on Thursday 04/24/25, Springerville Interagency Dispatch is located within the Supervisors Office. A Ticket was...",
    "narrative": "Internet went down here at the Springerville Supervisors Office on Thursday 04/24/25, Springerville Interagency Dispatch is located within the Supervisors Office. A Ticket was put in with CHD right away and it was confirmed that a frontier line had been cut. While the internet service was down at the SO, Dispatch radios still worked and our phones still worked but we did have to switch our computers over to our Verizon hotspots. At about 1200 on 04/29/2025 dispatch lost radio and phone service. This is a huge safety issue as we have no way of communicating with resources other than using our personal or GOV cell phones. While writing up this safenet we are currently getting lightning on the west side of our forest. We are getting multiple IA's daily within the White Mountain Zone including the Apache-Sitgreavs NFs and Fort Apache Agency.",
    "immediateAction": "Placed a ticket with CHD today 04/29/2025. Sent out a text via wildcad letting all our resources know we have zero communication other than cell phone. Contacted individual Duty Officers to have them track district resources for the time being. Local radio tech has been made aware of the situation and is going to contact frontier direct to see what time frames we are looking at.  The GACC and all neighboring forests have been notified of our situation.",
