    "snippet": "The radio's at Alabama Interagency Coordination Center went down for 20 minutes today. The dispatch office wasn't able to communicate with anyone in the field during those 20...",
    "narrative": "The radio's at Alabama Interagency Coordination Center went down for 20 minutes today. The dispatch office wasn't able to communicate with anyone in the field during those 20 minutes. We reached out to the Forest Radio Tech and received no answer, and we attempted to leave a voicemail, but the radio tech voicemail was full. We have had multiple radio issues this spring fire season. There have also been multiples times where we have reached out to the appropriate individuals to get these radio issues resolved and failed to get ahold of anyone. The incident with the radio going down today on 04/17/2025 happened while resources were working on an RX. Not having proper communication with resources during a hazardous activity such as this one is a major concern and hazard. Not being able to get ahold of the radio tech during this sort of event is a major hazard/issue. ¿¿¿¿¿¿¿",
    "immediateAction": "To mitigate this unsafe event, we used a remote dispatcher on the Talladega NF and had him cover all repeaters on the forest until the radio's were back up here in the dispatch center. We also alerted all of the distrcts and told them to call dispatch if they were having trouble reaching dispatch on the radios.",
