    "snippet": "While enroute from our duty station to the briefing area I had a near miss on a bridge along Highway 70 in the Feather river canyon. it was approximately 0820 I was traveling...",
    "narrative": "While enroute from our duty station to the briefing area I had a near miss on a bridge along Highway 70 in the Feather river canyon. it was approximately 0820 I was traveling west at 45 MPH on state route 70 when I came to a narrow bridge, the Tobin bridge. there is a right hand turn emedietly proceeding the bridge, making hard to see where vehicles are possitioned on the bridge. As I came around the corner and on to the bridge there was a large service type truck on the bridge. this truck had his duals over the yellow line. in order to avoid him I gently moved the engine as far right as I could while slowly braking. my focus was on the guardrail along the right side of the bridge as I was trying to move as far right as possible. on the model 326 side discharge there was a 1.5 inch gated wye. this gated wye clipped part of the guard rail and broke away. after crossing the bridge I emmediatly pulled over to inspect the vehicle, i did not find any damage to the vehicle, and see if the service type truck stopped. they did not. after looking over the truck and determining there was no damage, I continued to the briefing.",
    "immediateAction": "The immediate actions taken were to slow down even more as I came to other bridges. I do not think speed was an issue, but rather the nature of not being able to accurately determine the position of on coming traffic on the bridge.",
