    "snippet": "We have had an issue with the Monongahela NF south zone repeater system, since 4/09/2025, which means that the entire south zone has no communications with our dispatch center....",
    "narrative": "We have had an issue with the Monongahela NF south zone repeater system, since 4/09/2025, which means that the entire south zone has no communications with our dispatch center. We have submitted multiple tickets for this issue.The radio technician is not on the forest and has not been able to get here to repair the system. March 1 through May 30 is our spring fire and prescribed fire season. We had a wildfire start on the south zone on 4/20, it quickly increase to a couple hundred acres and is threatening structure. We needed a helicopter, and had to patch together communications to keep them and the firefighters on the ground, multiple crews, engine and overhead, safe. I have contacted our radio technician and they are unable to travel until later in the week.",
    "immediateAction": "We have set up a portable repeater, but since the base radio's in the officer are voice override and part of the system that is down, we have someone out in our engine monitoring a conventional base radio. And dispatch still can not hear anything, we have to call in any request, and they are unable to follow resources for us.",
