    "snippet": "The Forest Service has been switching over network providers recently at the Monongahela NF facilities. On 3/28/2025, after the network had been switched over, it was discovered...",
    "narrative": "The Forest Service has been switching over network providers recently at the Monongahela NF facilities. On 3/28/2025, after the network had been switched over, it was discovered that the radio system covering the North Zone of the forest was no longer working. Previous to this, the forest was dealing with an ongoing intermittent radio outage on the North Zone as well. Not having a reliable and or working radio network has put our forest employees and emergency responders in a non-safe position. Any new fire reported will receive a delayed response until we can evaluate the situation and ensure the 'C' in LCES can be established.",
    "immediateAction": "CIO Radio Tech was notified and remote testing was done to troubleshoot the problem. It is their opinion that an 'IP 244' needs to replace on-site. CIO Radio Tech has stated they would be available on 3/31/2025 to walk someone through replacing that part. A CEC Remedy ticket was also submitted on 3/29/2025. All field going fire employees, the dispatch center and Line Officers have been made aware of our inability to communicate over the radio system in the north zone. Due to the remoteness of the forest and largely varied terrain, cell-phone coverage is nearly unattainable in the majority of the forest.",
