    "snippet": "On Tuesday March 25, 2025 at approximately 15:00 hours, a firefighter working with a crawler tractor constructing indirect containment line on the Black Cove Complex Fire was...",
    "narrative": "On Tuesday March 25, 2025 at approximately 15:00 hours, a firefighter working with a crawler tractor constructing indirect containment line on the Black Cove Complex Fire was struck by a dead standing snag after the snag was uprooted by a crawler tractor's forward movement. The firefighter was struck by the snag on their shoulder, knocked to the ground and the tree came to rest on their lower leg. Fireline leadership responded to the scene and initiated the IWI Protocol set forth by the IMT which included the use of the Medical Incident Report (8-Line.) The need for remote extraction was determined due to the nature of injury and patient mobility. The firefighter was extracted from the injury site by an NCHART helicopter and flown to advanced medical care.A 24 hour report was issued on 3/26/2025. To date (10/14/2025) no 72 hour report, final report, or additional details have been provided to agency personnel. 24 hour, 72 hour, and final reports are required by NCFS Accident Lessons Learned Reporting SOP issued 9/12/2024.  These reports are critical to prevent misinformation, facilitate lessons learned training, guide future risk management decisions, and identify hazardous conditions and actions on the fireline.",
