    "snippet": "Loss of link to NC-NCC Radio System towers (Scaley and Joanna repeaters) While on going initial attack activity is high, The net work circuit being down to bolt tower is a know...",
    "narrative": "Loss of link to NC-NCC Radio System towers (Scaley and Joanna repeaters) While on going initial attack activity is high, The net work circuit being down to bolt tower is a know issue that affects safe and effective Comminutions needed, Not only at the coordination center but the operations in the field with crews, aviation, resources, This has been an on going issue since 2018 when the switch from Modu Comm to voice over IP radio system occurred The Critical ticket was placed with the CEC Critical/High REQ000005185220 on 03/18/2025 to try and establish communications on the Towers effected by the loss of link by provider, no resolve from the CEC or the provider and issue is on going   The switch over to voice over IP has had dangerous effects to the safety and tracking of resources, While conducting not only initial attack and extended attack fires here at the North Carolina Coordination center, It has also effected the Flight following and tracking of aviation resources, These resources can not communicate with the coordination center while in special use airspace which effects the safety of the aviation crew members",
    "immediateAction": "Ground resources maintained communication on tack frequencies, NCNCC and fire staff officer established an ABRO position with helicopter crewmembers assigned to the aviation resources prepositioned here for initial attack, Currently have a critical tickets open with CEC Network  REQ000005185220  and reported to the forest fire staff officer and risk management staff at the regional office to take action on issues with the voice over IP radio system transition",
