    "snippet": "We have had constant issues since the Lumen switch over. Intermittent outages, overall slowness, The ability to open some applications but not others. For instance, we currently...",
    "narrative": "We have had constant issues since the Lumen switch over. Intermittent outages, overall slowness, The ability to open some applications but not others. For instance, we currently have been operating on WIFI all week because the network is up (and per CIO apparently has no issues) However, You can get into FAMAuth but only certain applications will open from there (i.e. IROC opens but WildCAD-e wont) AFF wont open, Microsoft Teams or office will open some days but not the next.At least once a month at a minimum, the whole network goes out which takes everything down, including phones which takes down the CALFIRE business lines as they are on our phone system as well.These are the specific resources currently being affected and what I shared with the OCIO-CEC IT specialist I was chatting with who elevated to ENS…So we can login to FAMAuth here https://famauth.wildfire.gov/?PAGENAV=dashboard to access our daily applications but only some work, Like IROC https://iroc.nwcg.gov/ works, but WILDCAD-e https://wildcade.firenet.gov/ does not. AFF does not work https://www.aff.gov/ Microsoft 365 i can log into with my USDA but then when in, I can’t open Microsoft Teams https://teams.microsoft.com/I manage an Emergency Command Center (Dispatch) that requires reliable network connectivity to multiple computer applications. Having network issues that either won't work at all or limits what applications you can access is unacceptable and becomes a huge safety issue to our firefighters and law enforcement officers. In the middle of fire season, I would think tracking aircraft is of the highest importance to have these systems up and functioning for safety. We have Law Enforcement making public contacts, resources being sent to incidents and we can barely keep our cad up and running.",
    "immediateAction": "Immediate on site trouble shooting to the best of our ability. We have had multiple tickets open through CHD with CIO, Only to be told every time that they see no issue or it has been resolved, only to happen again in a short time later or being told to simply 'power cycle' the router or switch.",
