    "snippet": "Responding to WUI Fire. South Carolina forestry commission requested assistance to a wildfire threating structures. SC Forestry commission had a 30 Minute response time before...",
    "narrative": "Responding to WUI Fire. South Carolina forestry commission requested assistance to a wildfire threating structures. SC Forestry commission had a 30 Minute response time before being on scene. IA group responded from Bradly work center to the fire approximately 4 minutes from Bradly Work Center. Leaving Bradly work center to the scene. I could not get any radio communication to dispatch and to notify dispatch that the IA group was responding to the incident. I could hear the carrier tone work but no communication to Columbia Dispatch. Trying multiple times with different radios hitting Parsons mountain repeater, still no communication with Columbia Dispatch. I am Concerned with current radio communication on the forest with Parson's Mountain and Liberty repeaters is not reliable, not working and inadequate for incident response. If an accident happens during a all risk incident or any other accident the only option is to rely on cell phone communication. If cellular coverage is not available this could delay or prevent a response and increase severity of the incident. Cell phone towers have been known to be down multiple times and days for maintenance and repairs. There is no back up communication for emergencies and all risk incidents. I know we can do better job with communications when our local partners and cooperators have no radio issues and can talk farther distances to their dispatch centers.",
