    "snippet": "Upon notiifcation of a wildfire via cell phone from a forest service employee, I could not reach any IA resource or dispatch via the repeaters. Repeaters would open up but no...",
    "narrative": "Upon notiifcation of a wildfire via cell phone from a forest service employee, I could not reach any IA resource or dispatch via the repeaters. Repeaters would open up but no transmission would go. Contacted all IA resources via phone and text as well as dispatch. Enroute notified FFMO and Fire Staff of the issue. Once on scene resources where briefed on lack of communications, cell service was checked and IA proceeded.This is not a radio issue, it is in the FS system. I can use my handhelds and mobile to talk to the SC Forestry Commission Dispatch 100 miles away and I can communicate with 4 EOC centers. Just can not talk with FS Dispatch.",
    "immediateAction": "Notified Dispatch, District Ranger, Fire Staff and Forest FMO of the issues and told them we would be doing a safe net. Ensures that LCES was in place with tac channels, cell phones and county coverage and proceeded with IA.",
