    "snippet": "Phones started malfunctioning last Thursday evening (2/27) with intermittent outages, we were not able to place calls out but could receive, by Friday morning the phones were...",
    "narrative": "Phones started malfunctioning last Thursday evening (2/27) with intermittent outages, we were not able to place calls out but could receive, by Friday morning the phones were operating normally. The issue started again Saturday, and seemed to correct itself again. By Monday 3/3, the phones were intermittent again and finally failed. The phones were manually reset multiple times from here in the office but that didn’t work. Ticket was submitted and floor personnel have been working with CIO. As of yesterday 3/5, the help desk elevated the ticket. This morning 3/6, help desk said phone company stated system is back and needs reboot. Tried reboot and still nothing. The help desk was told that were supporting a prescribed fire as well as active wildfires. Currently we are operating off the duty phone and email for any needs.",
    "immediateAction": "Tried to reboot the system.Contacted CIO help desk an submitted ticket.CM Notidied Forest fire leadership about issue.Mass texted fire personnel via WildCAD that phone lines were down and to contact Centers after hours phone number during day if they needed to get in contact with VIC. Periodically tested phones to see if they were working. Did radio tests with Forest communication technician to ensure Dispatch center was able to communicate with field resourcesCM notified geographic coordination center that main line phone was non-operational.",
