    "snippet": "Phones started malfunctioning last Thursday evening (2/27) with intermittent outages, we were not able to place calls out but could receive, by Friday morning the phones were...",
    "narrative": "Phones started malfunctioning last Thursday evening (2/27) with intermittent outages, we were not able to place calls out but could receive, by Friday morning the phones were operating normally. The issue started again Saturday and seemed to correct itself again. By Monday 3/3, the phones were intermittent again and finally failed. The phones were manually reset multiple times from here in the office but that didn’t work. A ticket (8669677) was put in and we have been working with CIO. As of 3/5, the help desk elevated the ticket. The help desk was told that were supporting a prescribed fire as well as active wildfires. We have been operating off the duty phone - one cell phone and email for any needs. On 3/7 Mettel came out and they reset a different part of the system and told us it was 'really old'. The phones worked until the morning of 3/9 and were out again, when we received a call it would drop after a few seconds and if we tried to call out we got a busy signal. The system was reset twice and after some time has come back up. A new ticket was submitted (5166157). In 2024 6 tickets were submitted for these same phone issues. Our concerns are that the system has had so many repeated problems that seem to only temporarily get fixed. The problems seem to be coming more frequently and taking longer to fix. It is interfering with our ability to have consistent communication with both resources and reporting parties. The duty cell phone is not enough to rely on as our only phone, especially during fire season.",
    "immediateAction": "We have been operating off the duty phone - one cell phone and email for any needs. Resources have been kept updated about the outage by text via WildCAD. The phones were manually reset multiple times from here in the office.",
