    "snippet": "Kisatchie Ranger District has been without phones, radio, and internet for over a month.  We are relying on personal cell phone hotspots and two field-use mifi units for...",
    "narrative": "Kisatchie Ranger District has been without phones, radio, and internet for over a month.  We are relying on personal cell phone hotspots and two field-use mifi units for internet.  To print documents we have to save to a usb device and take it to a local printer.  During this time the district has had several incidences where public emergencies were not able to be reported directly to the office. The office houses the only Agency Administrator for two districts which have had around 15 wildfires and 15 prescribed burns totaling tens of thousands of acres. Communications are life and death at this office. Radios are down due to the site being down and this is causing extreme safety concerns. This is causing major safety concerns for firefighters having to drive 40+ miles away from prescribed burns, or wildfire areas to relay information. Customers in the area are unable to contact the office for information and safety related issues. Cell coverage in the area is almost non-existent. Internet, radios, and landlines are the bloodline for this office and its forest coverage area.",
    "immediateAction": "We have put in many tickets to get these issues resolved to no avail.  We have been using government and personal cell phone hotspots for internet.  We have also been using two mifi units intended for field-use only for internet.  Other offices have been receiving phone calls from the public and relaying the calls to our cell phones.  Response to public emergencies have been delayed due to the inability to contact our office.  Eventually, those incidences have gone through 911 and the Sheriff's Department contacts my cell phone.",
    "mgmtLevel": "N/A",
    "task": "District communications",
