    "snippet": "On 1-12-25 at we pulled into the Malibu camp for the Palasides fire after our shift. We noticed a area that appeared to be a sleeping area. We asked a CCC member if that was the...",
    "narrative": "On 1-12-25 at we pulled into the Malibu camp for the Palasides fire after our shift. We noticed a area that appeared to be a sleeping area. We asked a CCC member if that was the sleeping area in which he said yes and that they also set up their tents there. As I walked up to the sleeping area I noticed it was fenced in three sides and the entrance was marked with traffic cones and flagging strung out between the cones. I noticed the CCC had about twenty tents set up and porta potty with a hand wash station. On 01-13-25 after shift we went back to the same sleeping area. The area was still blocked off with cones and the CCC still had their tents up. At 2100 I was awakened by a water tender watering the sleeping area. I approached him to inform him that this was a sleeping area and that it's was not safe to be in the area because there is multiple firefighters sleeping. He quickly apologized and said he will leave. He said he knew it was unsafe but the base camp manager told him to water the area. On 1-14-25 I was awakened again at 0600 by a strike team of engines driving into the area and parking next to me. I noticed someone placed cones around me and other firefighters who where still sleeping. I gathered my stuff and went to talk to the base camp manager. I found the base camp manager and told him of the situation. He explained to me that they ran out of parking spots and needed more for engines the decision was made to use the sleeping area as a parking area. He informed he knew we were there and he mitigated the Hazzard by placing traffic cones around the sleeping firefighters. I felt like he didn't understand the seriousness of the issue so I talked to the logistics chief who told me the same thing the base camp manager said. When I was awakened by that strike team that morning one engine got within 5 feet of me as I was gathering my belongings. This was a very unsafe situation that should of never happened.",
    "immediateAction": "I will be finding my own sleeping area and making sure it's well marked off.",
    "mgmtLevel": "1",
    "task": "Camp sleeping area",
    "resources": "ANF TF 1600",
