    "snippet": "I have put a SafeNet in last week regarding our Networking infrastructure, the Internet Provider repaired the missing Copper line at 0800 on the 15th of Oct by 1530 on the 15th...",
    "narrative": "I have put a SafeNet in last week regarding our Networking infrastructure, the Internet Provider repaired the missing Copper line at 0800 on the 15th of Oct by 1530 on the 15th of OCT the Copper line providing internet services was stolen by local members of the community which brought down our radio communications with our district to our dispatch center. The internet company told us that we are the only customers using the Copper line internet and everyone else in the community is now on Fiber Optics and they stated this could be an ongoing issue in the future. They fixed the Line on the 16th again and we have been fortunate to have Networking work in our office for our computers and phones. The unfortunate part of this is we still do not have Communication with our Dispatch Center I have been working with our radio tech on our forest to figure out what is the new issue, the repeaters are talking to each other but the link between the repeaters and the IP224 is not working which is leaving our field going folks dark with dispatch.This lack of continuous communication presents a huge safety issue, we cannot call out on our radios to dispatch for incident size ups, potential life threating events or even to request ambulance. Our district has horrible cell service so even if we could call 911 to get help odds are it won't work to limited cell coverage.We are getting really close to our most active part of the fire season with multiple resources coming in from other parts of the country and the wildfire responses are going to continue to climb and we don't have radios that can work correctly due to the networking issues we are having.",
    "immediateAction": "I have filed a SafeNet once this year and there were multiple filed last year by other folks regarding our Radio issues and Networking on the Redbird Purchase Unit.I will continue to File SafeNet's until this is resolved, we on the district are getting tired of this safety issue that is ongoing regarding lack of communication it is a huge Watch Out Situation. We are missing our C in LCES and that should throw red flags to folks in the Regional Office and the Washington Office. There needs to be some other alternative to fix the system we have in place now so based off the question for this box (please describe actions you took to correct or mitigate the unsafe even), in the field we are trying to figure it out, CIO and WO need to come up with solutions to help keep us safe and return the C in LCES.I will provide contact information due to the importance of this issue",
    "mgmtLevel": "N/A",
