    "snippet": "With the rugged Terrain in SE Kentucky, local winds and other local factors(public) our powerlines and internet are on power poles. Currently and very frequent our internet is...",
    "narrative": "With the rugged Terrain in SE Kentucky, local winds and other local factors(public) our powerlines and internet are on power poles. Currently and very frequent our internet is nonoperational. This internet supplies our direct connection to our Forest Dispatch via the IP224 consul from our repeaters, so when the internet goes down, we lose contact with our dispatch center. From trees falling on our powerlines to local public cutting the Networking cables for the copper inside of the lines.We have reached out to the Internet company with no success on prioritizing our request due to safety and response to wildfires. The safety issue is when we lose the internet due to the factors listed above, we don't have contact with dispatch on wildfires. This is a safety issue; we sent our folks out to fight fire without having a lifeline via dispatch there is no way to call in an IWI or assistance with an ongoing incident. There is very limited cell service in Southeast Kentucky especially on the Redbird.",
    "immediateAction": "We have Made contact with the local provider. we currently are using Garmin InReach devices as an emergency communication tool.Suggestions are if possible, to move our Networking to a low-level satellite-based internet provider for our important communication system and get away from a land based (power pole copper wire) system that is currently in place.",
