    "snippet": "On Wednesday, September 25, 2024, at 1615 the Durango Tanker Base lost network connectivity which removed Durango Interagency Dispatch’s ability to communicate via radio with two...",
    "narrative": "On Wednesday, September 25, 2024, at 1615 the Durango Tanker Base lost network connectivity which removed Durango Interagency Dispatch’s ability to communicate via radio with two zones (San Juan NF Central zone off of the Smelter repeater base and Southern Ute off of the SUA base) and the Tanker Base itself via phones. The Dispatch center was told to wait until the following morning (Thursday 9/26) to submit a ticket in the hopes that the network would reset overnight. The network did not reset, and a ticket was submitted. The Radio Technician preformed an on-site inspection of the Durango Tanker Base confirming power, and the Forest equipment was working correctly.  Per the ticket information received on Friday, 9/27, the issue has been sent to AT&T. Durango Interagency Dispatch has not been able to communicate with field resources since Wednesday night. We have several prescribed fires continuing on both national forest and BLM lands with multiple resources moving across the dispatch zone to and from their home units to those prescribed fires, or to initial attacks that maybe occurring throughout the dispatch zone. The San Juan National Forest is beginning a drying trend with an uptick in resource use as visitor use increase into the weekend for leaf peeping, and hunting. Fixing the network and restoring voice over IP is critical in ensuring safe ground operations as we move into the weekend.",
    "immediateAction": "A ticket was created and placed per agency ticket workflow. The issue was deemed to be a network outage and transferred to AT&T.",
