    "snippet": "There are a couple of teams being hosted by the Boise NF that seem to be lacking leadership. Specifically West Mountain complex and Middle Fork complex. 1. TFRs that do not...",
    "narrative": "There are a couple of teams being hosted by the Boise NF that seem to be lacking leadership. Specifically West Mountain complex and Middle Fork complex. 1. TFRs that do not correlate with the values assigned to the individual teams. This has resulted in aircraft and personnel being pulled off the line while in the middle of suppression activity’s, on pre-identified alignments. 2. Teams and AAs can’t seem to communicate effectively enough for resolve in this matter.With “neighboring” fire less than 1 mile away from life and property, incident resources have been limited / prohibited, from taking any action early on, resulting in unnecessary exposure.  3. Unclear and rapidly changing circumstances leading to the personnel being inserted, removed and inserted again. While fire personnel on the ground found ways to communicate with adjoining fire and resolve threatening fire behavior concerns, these efforts would be thwarted somewhere up the chain of command. Understanding that wildland fire is a rapidly evolving and dynamic environment, the lack of actions by either team to resolve this matter was unacceptable. Fire in the local area saw unprecedented rates of spread. During these events, Incident Management Teams need to be resolute when it comes to incident personnel safety and delegated objectives.",
    "immediateAction": "Multiple calls to operations and ICs from both teams. Presenting favorable plans with low risk options.",
