    "factors": [
      "Communications"
    ],
    "snippet": "ON 9/3 IN THE MORNING RADIO COMMUNICATIONS ON THE ODF REPEATERS TO INCLUDE BOTH THE JOHN DAY AND FOSSIL SUB UNITS OF THE CENTRAL OREGON DISTRICT STOPPED WORKING.  AT 1430  WE...",
    "narrative": "ON 9/3 IN THE MORNING RADIO COMMUNICATIONS ON THE ODF REPEATERS TO INCLUDE BOTH THE JOHN DAY AND FOSSIL SUB UNITS OF THE CENTRAL OREGON DISTRICT STOPPED WORKING.  AT 1430  WE LOST COMMUNICATIONS ON OUR FEDERAL FLIGHT FOLLOWING FREQUIENCIES WITH AIRCRAFT FLYING ACTIVE INCIDENTS, WE ALSO LOST COMMUNICATIONS ON THE FEDERAL EAST NET REPEATERS.",
    "immediateAction": "WE CONTACTED THE LOCAL RADIO TECH FOR THE FOREST AND THE ODF RADIO TECH. THHE CAME IN AND HEADED UP TO THE FALL MOUNTAIN BASE SITE. WE HAD COMMS VIA PHONE WITH THE AIR ATTACK AND NOTIFIED HIM OF THE ISSUES, AND THE HELICOPTERS FLYING CONTACTED A NEIGHBORING DISPATCH CENTER. WITH AIR ATTACK BEING IN THE AIR WE WERE ABLE TO GET HIM ONTO A WORKING REPEATER TO ESTABLISH COMMUNICATIONS. THE INCIDENTS WE HAD NO RADIO COMMS WITH WERE ABLE TO TALK MOBILE TO MOBILE AND PUT A HUMAN REPEATER IN PLACE TO CONTACT US VIA CELL PHONE. FOR THE EMERGING INCIDENT TWO CABINS WE NOTIFIED OF RADIO COMMUNICATION ISSUES AND THEY WERE ABLE TO MOVE TO THE WORKING FOREST REPEATER. A RADIO TICKET WAS CREATED INC #820535THE RADIO TECHS GOT TO THE SITE AND FOUND THAT THERE WAS A POWER FAILURE, THE POWER COMPANY WAS CONTACTED WITH AN UNSURE TIME OF WHEN THEY WOULD BE ABLE TO FIX IT. THE TECHS HOOKED THE RADIO POWER UP TO A  VEHICLE TO GET IT WORKING AS A SHORT TERM SOLUTION UNTIL A GENERATOR COULD BE PURCHASED TO FIX IT UNTIL POWER COMPANY COULD FIX IT. A GENERATOR WAS PURCHASED, BUT THE POWER COMPANY ARRIVED AND FIXED THE ISSUE AROUND 1730 ALL RADIOS WERE BACK TO BEING FUNCTIONAL.AT ABOUT 2300 WE STARTED EXPERIENCING SIMILAR RADIO ISSUES. AT 0700 CALLS WERE PUT BACK INTO RADIO TECHS TO CHECK TO MAKE SURE POWER IS STILL ESTABLISHED AT BASE SITE THIS IS ON GOING AND WAITING FOR A SOLUTION. ALL INCIDENTS AND UNITS HAVE BEEN NOTIFIED AND WORKING ON WORK AROUND TO STAY FUNCTIONAL FOR THE DAY UNTIL THIS IS FIXED.A NOTE TO ADD IS THE RADIO TECHS DID AN AMAZING JOB AND WERE SUPER HELPFUL AND SUPPORTIVE. THERE WERE NO WARNINGS OR NOTIFICATIONS OF POWER GOING OUT. DUE TO THE NATURE OF THE INCIDENT AND LOSS OF COMMUNICATIONS ON ACTIVE INCIDENTS A SAFENET NEEDED TO FILED.",
    "mgmtLevel": "4",
