    "snippet": "Crozier fire camp sleeping area for fed and contract resources was located on a race track at the fair grounds. In the sleeping area there were blue rooms. At approximately 2130...",
    "narrative": "Crozier fire camp sleeping area for fed and contract resources was located on a race track at the fair grounds. In the sleeping area there were blue rooms. At approximately 2130 while people were sleeping a pumper truck entered the sleeping area driving around the track to clean and pump the blue rooms among sleeping people. The next day I brought it to the attention of a member of the cal fire team and he said he would pass it along and it would be taken care of. The next night the truck entered but stayed close to the gate and drove around out side the track out side the sleeping area with minimal exposure to people sleeping. A few days later 8/14 they moved the sleeping area to new location. This occasion the truck entered the sleeping area again pumping three blue room locations in the sleeping area among sleeping people. It backed up multiple times with out using a backer. They were confronted about the situation but continued about there business. The team has patrollers telling people they can not sleep out side the sleeping area however it seems not to be the safest place to sleep. This has happened before and people have been run over in sleeping areas. In addition there is also a hand washing station that was maintained around 2100 by a vehicle entering the sleeping area as well.",
    "immediateAction": "I slept through the first incident and apparently the truck drove rite by me. I reported it to the team the next morning at briefing and it seemed some form of corrective action was taken. The last time another person confronted the truck at the gate and they continued to drive thru the sleeping area. I felt like Safenet was the best option I had left to report this unnecessary hazard as at least 2 of us have not been herd in our concerns.",
