    "snippet": "The centennial repeater for the rocky boy agency fire management office that links to our dispatch center is non operable. We noticed on July 21, 2024 roughly around 1300 that...",
    "narrative": "The centennial repeater for the rocky boy agency fire management office that links to our dispatch center is non operable. We noticed on July 21, 2024 roughly around 1300 that communication between engine staff and dispatch was either broken or unreadable. Over the next few days we noticed the traffic was starting to drop off. This morning 08/01/2024 0845 we contacted hi-line communications to schedule a repair visit. Technician Steve, owner of hi-line communications verified the outage and explained to us the main source problem was due to a power issue with the problem being a bad power connection in the main conduit line from the northwest energy meter box to the building that houses our repeater and tribal roads repeater. During todays tribal business committee meeting it was brought to their attention by the BIA representative and a solution was to be made by the end of the business day 08/01/2024 to remedy the issue as soon as possible to restore the centennial repeater to operation.  As of this morning we are working on a back up plan to switch over to the tribal roads repeater, but at the same time tribal roads repeater is housed in the same building as fire managements repeater but the tribal roads repeater seems to be working at this time.We are concerned for our firefighters safety due to lack of communications if we was to get a large wildfire, as we are on short term severity for the rocky boy annual pow wow. Dispatch, management, tribal council, and firefighters know communication is an issue and that it needs to be corrected as soon as possible.",
    "immediateAction": "Fire fighting resources are using their cell phones to communicate with dispatch and we are going to try cloning are radios and mobile radios to the tribal roads repeater.",
