    "snippet": "I was notified on Friday morning (7/19) at about 0730 that the phones were not working in the center, no calls in, no calls out.  I advised the dispatch zone resources via...",
    "narrative": "I was notified on Friday morning (7/19) at about 0730 that the phones were not working in the center, no calls in, no calls out.  I advised the dispatch zone resources via WildCAD text and email of the outage and advised them of alternate contact information .  I called in to the FS Helpdesk and initiated help desk ticket number INC000008148559. I also advised the Help Desk that we had several active fire incidents and it was an urgent.  After the help desk ticket was submitted, I received a call from one the techs that asked me to go reset the phone switch, which I did and it didn't fix the problem, he advised he would push the ticket up and it was a elevated as critical due to fire season. By about 1200 I called the tech back he advised that he had made all the appropriate notifications, and then notified again of the critical issue. I never heard from anyone.  This morning 7/20 I contacted the help desk again to check the status of the ticket. I found out that it was still pending, even though it was at a Sev1 and no one had been assigned the ticket.  Since it is handled by contractors it will not even be touched until Monday.  We are in the middle of fire season, we have active incidents with ground resources and aviation resources working.  We have one dispatch cell phone for the entire floor and could be catastrophic if we get a lightning storm on the zone have a bunch of new starts.  It will delay a response from ground and aviation resources and could cause fire incidents to get out control damaging property, resources, and life safety.  This whole situation is unacceptable, a safety issue of epic proportion, does not allow for the dispatchers in this center to provide service to the public or take care of the  boots on the ground or the aviation resources that are already risking their lives and safety.",
    "immediateAction": "There has been no resolution yet, however we were able to order a cell phone kit from CDK that will provide us more than one phone into dispatch.",
