    "snippet": "While involved in intensive and high tempo fire suppression operations, several radio transmissions occured on identified tactical channels which then occurred on command...",
    "narrative": "While involved in intensive and high tempo fire suppression operations, several radio transmissions occured on identified tactical channels which then occurred on command channels. This seemed to only occur during periods of intense fire fighting operations with rapid communication exchange between fire resources on the firelines. These instances involved all levels of divisional resources as well as branches, air ops and field ops. These transmissions interrupted critical communications which would have typically occurred on command channels, handicapping critical communication exchange between fire personnel. Fire resources were inadvertently walking on each other without their knowledge because of radio selector knobs being on identified tactical channels. Line safety from previous team who had extended, identified this issue occurring during a yellow IWI where communication on command where radio traffic was interrupted.",
    "immediateAction": "Line safeties identified communication issues and elevated it to lead team safety who then engaged communications unit lead. Communications lead was perplexed by situation and took extra time to investigate why this would have been happening. After several hours they discovered what appeared to be a master program feature which had been enabled with newer BKR5000 and KNG2 cache radios. Mitigating factors included reprogramming via computer vs clone and limiting rapid communication by pausing for several seconds when transmitting. Further action should be taken for any national cache radios. Issue will be communicated through a regional safety call directly to incident Safety functions in cooperation with Communication unit to alleviate issue in real time. Working with regional risk management specialist to develop RLS for national distribution.",
    "mgmtLevel": "N/A",
