    "snippet": "This safety issues occurred with with decision of CAL FIRE to split off and create their own camp away from the existing IMT/Fire Camp on the Lake incident. Cal Fire is also...",
    "narrative": "This safety issues occurred with with decision of CAL FIRE to split off and create their own camp away from the existing IMT/Fire Camp on the Lake incident. Cal Fire is also splitting the fire into SRA controlled land and FED DPA controlled land with two different com plans/command channels. This is a recipe for disaster with the communication on and off the fire line. The lake fire communications between CAL FIRE and Santa Barbara County and USFS has been horrible with state wanting to run the ordering/communication one way while the IMT try's to run it their way. Cal FIRE seems to push themselves in and their only concern is their own agency. This divorce of leadership and chain of command has delayed ordering of resources, aircraft and logistics. It as also resulted in some miss steps regarding some incident medicals. With the plan of two management teams in two different camp on two different command frequency splitting the fire into two areas of management(SRA with CAL FIRE) and the existing IMT management team running the FED DPA will cause a immense amount of confusion and communication breakdown. We will also see a slew of different priories all the while fighting over aircraft and suppression plans.",
