    "snippet": "During a  communications between DIV. and crew to determine crew location and assignment and talking to helco to determine location of a sling site  for water for the crew the...",
    "narrative": "During a  communications between DIV. and crew to determine crew location and assignment and talking to helco to determine location of a sling site  for water for the crew the channel selector knob on the BKR 5000 broke. Rendering the radio down to the frequency I was on and the frequency I had selected a priority. It is almost impossible to select a channel without the  channel selection  knob. I was able to pull the knob of another crew radio to replace mine.  No more than an hour later we had a yellow medical where coordination between  A/G Tac, A/G Command, DIV tac, Command, Calcord, and common use frequencies  were essential for rapid and safe patient extraction. If the selector Knob would have failed at this time it would have been  difficult to communicate with the needed resources.  It is almost impossible to turn the channel selector without the knob. The knob breaking is not uncommon we carry an extra bag of knobs just for this reason. In this instance  the replacements were inn a bag in the glove box of the Supt. truck we were spiked out. The knobs are also known to just fall off.",
    "immediateAction": "No individuals to report. This is an equiptment issue.",
