    "snippet": "The Assistant Fleet Manager for the Eldorado NF. Supplied an expired set of tires to a Dozer Tender #4950. The assistant fleet manager bypassed the Fleet Maintenance staff that...",
    "narrative": "The Assistant Fleet Manager for the Eldorado NF. Supplied an expired set of tires to a Dozer Tender #4950. The assistant fleet manager bypassed the Fleet Maintenance staff that is responsible for this type of service. When his supervisor was asked about this situation he lied and blamed it on Fleet Maintenance staff. The operator was then questioned, and he said no these tires were supplied by the assistant fleet manager and he said they weren't expired and within date.The Fleet Maintenance staff is the subject matter experts in this field, and is highly trained in policy and procedures for these maintenance scenarios, They weren't even contacted for approval. The Eldorado Fleet Managers aren't qualified or have the experience.For DOT application the expiration date for tires is six years. These tires are eleven years old and need to be disposed of.",
    "immediateAction": "The Tire Vendor saw the age of the tires and wouldn't install them.Then the Eldorado Fleet Manager asked if we could find another vendor to install them.At this point the Fleet Maintenance staff was involved, and said no. These tires are expired and need to be disposed of.",
