    "snippet": "A tentative offer was made to a tech on March 1st 2024 to fill the vacant Radio Technician position. The 30 day hiring freeze has spread to 3 months, and all hiring has started...",
    "narrative": "A tentative offer was made to a tech on March 1st 2024 to fill the vacant Radio Technician position. The 30 day hiring freeze has spread to 3 months, and all hiring has started except for Business which includes the Radio Technician position. During this time one of our main radio repeaters for the zone went down, a tower that is important to the incident this is filled under, the Spruce Creek Fire, which went Type 3 and had many crews, drones, and a helicopter assigned to it. There is currently no radio tech local to the San Juan National Forest. The closest techs are several hours away on other forests. Durango has a Hotshot Crew, a Helitack Crew a Tanker Base, three districts, and a dispatch center. As we head deeper in to fire season, it is a huge safety issue for the zone to not have a tech hired to the area. There have been other issues with radio programing as well as the ongoing tower issues that we need a tech on board to take care of.",
    "immediateAction": "The regional Supervisory Electronics Technician, has been pushing this issue up the chain as much as possible to get this position hired. He has also sent technicians from neighboring forests when able to get the repeater back in commission.",
