    "snippet": "5/14/2024Engine went to R8/9 Engine academy and was immediately red-tagged for multiple issues; some of which were broken welds on box/pump package**Had to get HME to agree with...",
    "narrative": "5/14/2024Engine went to R8/9 Engine academy and was immediately red-tagged for multiple issues; some of which were broken welds on box/pump package**Had to get HME to agree with completing the work under warranty at the agreed location, welding shop; during this time the engine was not used.8/20/24Engine was taken to the welding shop to have welds repaired.9/4/24Weld repair and adding strength to framework was approved by HME according to welder from the welding shop.10/22/24Engine picked up from the welding shop by an employee; brought to Cabool where an employee picked up and brought back to Houston, MO and he noticed that weld job was sub par.10/23/24Photos of weld work were taken – multiple burn spots on truck and welds, welds are sloppy, globby and even covered in a rubberized coating (potentially JB weld) and then spray painted chrome in some places. Integrity of metal is lessened in multiple weld locations due to holes being melted in the metal by welding.This poses a safety concern – this is the second time that the welds have had to been repaired on this engine and it seems the solution was just to add more material rather than taking the time to complete quality work. It is also my understanding that aluminum loses its integrity the more times it is welded or super heated, and that it is aluminum framing under the box/plumbing which means that there is more potential for weld failure in the future. This poses a safety concern not only for the operator but for the public as well, if the box were to come loose/off.Additionally, we haven’t been able to locate the added strength to the framework that the welding shop was supposed to add.",
    "immediateAction": "Currently the engine welds are holding up, two days after receiving the engine back from the shop. They are continuously being monitored multiple times a day as we are responding to and checking fires on district.Overhead has been contacted in regards to issue and it has been advised to monitor weld status.Photos of the welds have been documented.",
