    "snippet": "On the afternoon of 04/25/24, while conducting prescribed burning operations, the radio link through internet provider's network failed causing a loss of communication. Alternate...",
    "narrative": "On the afternoon of 04/25/24, while conducting prescribed burning operations, the radio link through internet provider's network failed causing a loss of communication. Alternate means of communication were established to track resources to complete burning operations and return assets to station safely. A CIO ticket was immediately placed and elevated with follow up communication to include forest and regional leadership. On 4/26/24, the service provider identified their issue and re-established repeater communications by 1030. A clear initial assessment of the failure, the severity, or potential cascade failures was never provided. Local LMR staff were able to only rule out their hardware. Until the service provider contacted local fire staff, there was no information available to guide further decisions. This lack of information affected wildland fire staffing plans, dispatch support and prescribed fire operations.",
    "immediateAction": "Initial notifications included Agency Administrators, Forest Supervisor, Land Mobile Radio Technician, Land mobile Radio Program Manager, Regional Duty Officer, Regional AD Operations and field staff. Mitigation actions included utilizing a district base station to access a portion of zone repeaters, contacting resources by cell / text, developing short and long term contingencies, placing a CIO ticket with leadership follow-ups and direct communications between field staff and network technicians.",
