    "snippet": "On 04/21/2024 firefighters were enroute to the vicinity of the airport where they would be flying out to return from assignment the next day. The total rainfall for the day was...",
    "narrative": "On 04/21/2024 firefighters were enroute to the vicinity of the airport where they would be flying out to return from assignment the next day. The total rainfall for the day was anticipated to be 0.75 inches and rain was actively falling pre, post and during the incident. A stop was made for lunch and following lunch a two car motor vehicle accident occurred in the parking lot. The parking lot was shared by multiple restaurants, businesses, and entertainment venues making it highly trafficked and larger in size.While attempting to leave the parking lot, a passenger vehicle was seen driving off any designated path at a high rate of speed and against other traffic not far from the firefighters vehcile. In order to evade being hit by said vehicle, the firefighter driving reacted and pulled forward only to be hit broadside by a separate oncoming vehicle. The impact occurred on the drivers side on the back 3/5 of the vehicle. No injuries were sustained by either party and both vehicles pulled to a safe area. Local law enforcement was then notified. During the event it was general situational awareness that triggered the driver to pull forward to avoid an accident. However, in reality during this event, the fight or flight aspect of human psychology was likely triggered decreasing the drivers overall situational awareness and ability to make decisions appropriate to the environment in its entirety. The result of this was still an accident, but with a vehicle other than the one which prompted the defensive behavior.",
    "immediateAction": "Directly following the motor vehicle collision I moved the vehicle out of traffics way and into a safe area. Following this I stepped out of the vehicle to insure the other party was able to also safely move out of the line of traffic. After getting a quick scene size up and knowing the other party was free of injuries, a call was made to dispatch for a two motor vehicle collision with no injuries. Notification was made to the firefighter whom the rental vehicles name was under, to the supervisor on the local district, and to the home unit supervisor. Following these notifications a call was made to the rental vehicle company in accordance with their procedures notifying them of the accident and associated damage. The vehicle was not moved from its safe spot post incident until being verbally cleared by Budget Rental Vehicle Staff to do so.",
    "mgmtLevel": "N/A",
    "task": "Transportation post assignment to return to home unit",
    "resources": "Rental Truck and Civilian Passenger Vehicle",
