    "snippet": "At approximately 1100 on 4/9/2024 there was a power surge at the VDOF Headquarters building where VICC is hosted. Shortly after, the FS network went down taking the radios and...",
    "narrative": "At approximately 1100 on 4/9/2024 there was a power surge at the VDOF Headquarters building where VICC is hosted. Shortly after, the FS network went down taking the radios and phones with it. VICC staff attempted to troubleshoot the issue by resetting the router/phone equipment on the first floor as well as the equipment in the basement. When that failed to resolve the issue a call was made to CIO to try to 'ping' the router. A ticket was also submitted, Ticket # 7874732. At approximately 1330 it was determined that the cause is a faulty media/fiber optic converter that is located in the basement. CIO will order the part however, it could be Friday 4/12 before it arrives and can be installed. When this outage occurred there was on prescribed fire in progress and one close to starting a test fire.",
    "immediateAction": "VICC staff attempted to trouble shoot the issue, then a call was made to CIO and a ticket submitted. Another staff member, who was on days off, went to the SO (2 hours away) to staff the backup dispatch console.",
