    "snippet": "On April 9th a ticket was placed that the Telex radios were not working. The Ticket was closed due to the Radio Shop stating that they couldn't get to the repeaters. We waited...",
    "narrative": "On April 9th a ticket was placed that the Telex radios were not working. The Ticket was closed due to the Radio Shop stating that they couldn't get to the repeaters. We waited until we could get to the repeater sites and contacted the Radio shop that they could now drive to the repeater site. They then said that they weren't sure it was the repeater but issues with trees. We then made arrangements to get fallers up to the repeater site to remove any obstructions of vegetation. They then said hold on they didn't know what the issue was and to not fall any trees. The branch chief made several contacts with them on how we can help to solve the issue. They have never been able to solve the problem. We now realize that the issue affects the whole west side of the Shasta Trinity NF. The Weather continued to get hotter and dryer with record temperatures. We are reaching the 98%-100% on the ERC's and are calling for Lightning at the end of this week. We cannot go into our lightning plan if we cannot use the Telex base stations.So we can't use handhelds or the Telex base stations to communicate with dispatch or resources. Anytime the dispatch center calls on the radio you can't pick them up on a handheld inside a building. The West Side of the Shasta Trinity NF has very limited cell phone coverage and to communicate with resources we need to have the ability to use the telex base stations especially when we go to a type three emerging incident on the unit.",
    "immediateAction": "I have talked to the Ranger and the Deputy Ranger as well as Chief 2. We have turned in tickets to CIO and have called and talked to the radio shop as well as personally talking with them one on one on how we might be able to fix the situation.",
    "mgmtLevel": "N/A",
