    "snippet": "During 2nd shift of the Teddy Bear Fire, I went to turn on my brand new BK KNG-2 P-150 radio that I had received a week prior to my assignment and it wasn't working. The screen...",
    "narrative": "During 2nd shift of the Teddy Bear Fire, I went to turn on my brand new BK KNG-2 P-150 radio that I had received a week prior to my assignment and it wasn't working. The screen was on and displayed channel 16 but the power knob was turned off and the dial was set at channel 1.  I took the battery off and put it back on.  It turned off the radio but would not turn back on.  The safety issue was not having communications with my resources during initial attack phase of the fire and for the rest of our 14 day assignment.",
