    "snippet": "On 3/30/2024 @ 2320 the power started flickering and the backup batteries for the 3 radio consoles at Virginia Interagency Dispatch Center (VA-VIC) started clicking. Internet and...",
    "narrative": "On 3/30/2024 @ 2320 the power started flickering and the backup batteries for the 3 radio consoles at Virginia Interagency Dispatch Center (VA-VIC) started clicking. Internet and radio consoles were down but the phones have remained connected. This morning at 0700 the FS network was still down affecting the internet and radio consoles. We have reset the FS server but radio consoles and internet are still down. A ticket has been placed and elevated by CIO. The importance of having communications during active fire operations was relayed but unknown when we will get a response from CIO.At 0930 CIO called back. Had us run some testing in the computer room. Tests were unsuccessful. Looks to be an FS network issue. Agent said it was being elevated and we should hear from them within the next 2 days.OUTAGE AFFECTSDaily Resource Operations: No ground or Aviation communications with dispatch. Ground crew field work. Incident check In/Out. Ground crews have work arounds in place but Aviation is grounded at this time due to inability to communicate with dispatch. Aviation is unable to fly affecting both GWJ NF and geographic requests.Currently Affected Incidents: An IA incident (Peaks 11 acres) that started yesterday evening and an extended attack incident (North Zone Complex which includes 5 Incidents, 15,977 acres).",
    "immediateAction": "Virginia Interagency Dispatch Center (VA-VIC) can only communicate with resources via telephone. Each district has placed a person acting as a RADO at each district office base station. VICC is using laptops that connect to the State of Virginia Wifi to run dispatch related programs including WildCAD-E and IROC. Aviation is grounded at this time due to inability to communicate with dispatch.",
    "mgmtLevel": "3",
