    "localUnit": "Alamogordo Dispatch, Oliver Lee State Park",
    "factors": [
      "Communications",
      "Equipment",
      "Environmental"
    ],
    "snippet": "During the early morning hours of 3/30/2024, around 00:30, our on-call dispatcher was alerted to a new start within our zone. The on-call dispatcher was contacted by the center...",
    "narrative": "During the early morning hours of 3/30/2024, around 00:30, our on-call dispatcher was alerted to a new start within our zone. The on-call dispatcher was contacted by the center manager, and the center manager stated that the duty officer had called him direct because the attempts to notify the dispatch center via phone were unsuccessful. Once the on-call dispatcher arrived at the center, they could not gain access through the main gate. After using a secondary entrance, the on-call dispatcher realized that the phones and radios at the center were not operational. It was later discovered that at some point during the night the power had gone out. The generators turned on like they were supposed to but when the main power came back on, the automatic switch that redirects power from the generators to the main line was not activated for the portion of the building that operates the radio and phone lines. Everything was functioning normally with the exception of the phones, radios, and the main gate. Fortunately, the new start was in an area that had cell phone coverage, so all of the communications on the incident were being handled via cell phone. Once the cause of the radio/phone outage was discovered, the switch was manually flipped, and power was restored to the phone and radio systems at around 07:30 that same morning. During the incident there was a 'Green' medical which was handled via cell phone and there were no apparent delays in the patient receiving medical care. Had this new start been in an area with no cell phone coverage, it would have been very difficult to communicate with resources in the field, if at all. There seems to be an issue with the generator system, thankfully this was not a more serious or involved incident or the outcome could have been much worse.",
    "immediateAction": "Resources on the Oliver Lee incident communicated with dispatch via cell phone. The switch to restore power to the phone/radio systems was manually flipped and normal operations were resumed.",
    "mgmtLevel": "4",
    "task": "Overnight initial attack dispatch.",
    "resources": "Dispatch Center, IHC, Engine Crews.",
