    "snippet": "On 3/29/24 MO-MOCC had 2 Dispatch computers become inoperable due to a Upgrade that was pushed at 1300 with no communication that it was happening.  This upgrade affected our...",
    "narrative": "On 3/29/24 MO-MOCC had 2 Dispatch computers become inoperable due to a Upgrade that was pushed at 1300 with no communication that it was happening.  This upgrade affected our Aircraft Desk and another Dispatch computer.  During the 1.5 hours that this upgrade was taking place these 2 computers were not able to be used during Initial Attack/Aircraft Dispatching and Tracking that we had going on on the Forest.  The upgrade was for IO-PROD-Win10(21H2).  When we contacted the Help Desk they were able to tell us that this Upgrade was behind schedule and that it was being pushed through to get everyone caught up.  This caused a Safety issue as for a short while we were unable to Safely Track our Aircraft using AFF or log any information in WILDCAD for the aircraft desk.",
    "immediateAction": "To mitigate this issue we swapped out computers so that the Aircraft Desk was able to use AFF and WILDCAD.  We also contacted the Help Desk to find out how long this was going to affect our computers and if any others were going to be affected.  After being on hold for the better part of 30 minutes with the Help Desk as they tracked down answers, they informed us that it was an update that was pushed do to the updates being behind schedule and there was nothing that could be done.  You can reference Help Desk Incident INC000007851300.",
    "mgmtLevel": "4",
