    "snippet": "The Kentucky Interagency Coordination Center (KICC) phones went out for the second time this week. This occurred at approximately 0200. A local division chief had received a call...",
    "narrative": "The Kentucky Interagency Coordination Center (KICC) phones went out for the second time this week. This occurred at approximately 0200. A local division chief had received a call from a local 911 center that there was a fire in the area near a fires location from the previous day. The Division chief attempted to call into dispatch to report the call and initiate a response but was unable to get through to the dispatcher on duty. KICC is 24 hour staffed. The division chief after multiple failed attempts ended up calling the duty officer phone. I was able to track the response via cell phone. As it was relayed to myself by CHD, our connection was moved over to an internet connection (not sure by whom, it might have been the carrier), in this move the MetTel phone system that we have lost all functionality. This is the second time this week that KICC and the SO have lost all phone functionality. Both times resulted in COOP requirements to be implemented to meet the needs of the local resources.",
    "immediateAction": "Cell phones, text messages, satellite communication devices were used to mitigate the issues. Additionally, personnel were required to use alternative methods of communication outside of normal channels to ensure proper tracking and resource accountability was maintained.",
