    "snippet": "The Black Mesa Ranger District consists of four repeaters. The Promontory Repeater sits on the Promontory Lookout. Last year, issues were raised regarding the repeater's...",
    "narrative": "The Black Mesa Ranger District consists of four repeaters. The Promontory Repeater sits on the Promontory Lookout. Last year, issues were raised regarding the repeater's ineffectiveness. Repairs were made, resulting in a slight improvement in its capabilities. This field season again has resulted in the repeater being highly deficient in its operating range. The district did a training scenario that consisted of a mock medical incident and communicating with dispatch. The training location was approximately 3.6 miles from the Promontory Repeater. The Promontory Repeater was unable to be used during the training. The individuals tried using the Gentry Repeater (14 miles away) and Chevelon Butte Repeater (25 miles away). They could utilize those repeaters, but due to the distance, communications with dispatch were ineffective and proved inadequate. That area receives thousands of recreators during the weekend and is a high-risk area for fires. The concern is that a fire or emergency in that area and the inability to communicate with dispatch or other resources pose a serious threat. I believe it is only a matter of time before that will occur. Cell phone service in that area is also very limited, resulting in no communications other than car-to-car channels.",
    "immediateAction": "Jimmy Riggs detailed FAFMO, actual Black Mesa RD DAFMO. District fire employees put in multiple tickets. INC000008000688 submitted by Aaron Ballesteros, INC000007962995 submitted by Rocky Nelson.",
